== Chiles Rellenos ==

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Halve @Poblano Pepper{2} lengthwise; remove stems and seeds. Drizzle each half with @Vegetable Oil{4%teaspoon}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place on a #baking sheet{} and roast on middle rack until softened, ~{15-17%minutes}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water (2 1/4 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil; cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Meanwhile, dice @Yellow Onion{1}(diced) and @Roma Tomato{1}(diced). Zest and quarter @Lime{1}(zested and quartered). Mince @Chili Pepper{1}(minced). In a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}, lime zest to taste, salt, and pepper. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably ovenproof, pan over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1}, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, half the tomato, 2 tablespoons water (¼ cup for 4 servings), salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir cooked rice into pan with veggies until thoroughly combined. Return pan to medium-high heat. Stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Turn off heat. Season with salt and pepper.

Once poblanos are roasted, stuff each half with as much filling as will fit. Nestle into pan with remaining filling.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture to a small baking dish and arrange stuffed poblanos in there.

Sprinkle poblano halves with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/2%cup}. Bake until cheese is melted and slightly crisp at edges, ~{7-8%minutes}.

== Avocado Salsa ==

Meanwhile, dice @Avocado{1}(diced). Toss in a #medium bowl{} with remaining tomato and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Divide filling and stuffed poblanos between plates. Top with avocado salsa, crema, and chili if desired. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> The crema is made from sour cream, lime zest, salt, pepper, and a little water to reach a drizzling consistency.